sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1151006

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Emanuele Rizzo

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1151014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a system, driven by the strong promoter pureA (BBa_K1151005), for the production of LuxR (BBa_C0062) by the addiction of nickel ions in medium and in presence of HpNikR (BBa_K1151000) as trascription factor. K1151005 + I0462
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Gabriele Alfarano

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1151015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A Hpn part (BBa_K1151001) (with RBS and terminator) is added at the end of the LuxI cds (BBa_ C0061). Hpn and LuxI depends both on the LuxpR promoter (BBa_R0062). The expression of this two protein is activated by LuxR (BBa_C0062) in concert with HSL. R0062 + C0261 B0034 + K1151001 + B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Gabriele Alfarano

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lux pR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Promoter activated by LuxR in concert with HSL

The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The right promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is up-regulated by the action of the LuxR activator protein complexed with the autoinducer, 3-oxo-hexanoyl-HSL. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules of the signalling compound homoserine lactone (HSL). This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This promoter is based on the Vibrio fischeri quorum sensing gene promoters. Two genes LuxI and LuxR and transcribed in opposite directions as shown below. The original sequence from which the parts BBa_R0062 and BBa_R0063 were derived is shown in the picture below.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LuxR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Produces LuxR protein which can sense 3OC<sub>6</sub>HSL in the media and activate transcription from R0062, the right hand Lux promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Caitlin Conboy and Jennifer Braff

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1151000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It was amplified by PCR from the genomic sequence of Helicobacter pylori G27.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The HpNikR protein is a pleiotropic regulator from Helicobacter pylori. In presence of nickel it can acts as an activator or a repressor depending of the specific promoter that contains its operator sites. Each monomer consists in 133aa for a molecular weight of approximately 17.2 kDa. Apo-HpNikR is a tetramer able to bind up to six Ni2+ ions and then a conformational change allows it to activate or repress trascription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was inserted in a pET-15b plasmid vector, in order to have a better storage.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Emanuele Rizzo

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1151001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: So called for emphasize its origins in Helicobacter pylori and its avidity for nickel. Consisting of 60 aminoacids, the protein is rich in histidine (28 residues, 46.7 %) and contains short repeating motifs, it exists as an equilibration of multimeric forms in solution, with 20-mers (approx. 136 kDa) being the predominant species. Hpn can bind tightly and reversibly up to five Ni2+ ions per each monomer of 7 kDa in a pH-dependent manner (pH 7.4 ). In H. pylori play an important role in storing nickel required to the survival of the bacterium.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The gene is designed on H.pylori genomic sequence and amplified by PCR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Davide Magr??

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1151005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was synthesized by IDT.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This promoter derived from ureAB operon of Helicobacter pylori. It can be linked by HpNikR (BBa_K1151000) in nickel presence for promoting trascription of the downstream gene
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Emanuele Rizzo

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: luxI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Synthesizes 3OC6HSL, which binds to LuxR.

The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The right promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is up-regulated by the action of the Lux repressor, LuxR. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules the signalling compound HSL. This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: An LVA tail (sequence: AANDENYALVA) was added to increase protein degradation. .
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: luxr
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
In complex with HSL, LuxR binds to the Lux promoter, activating transcription from Pr BBa_R0062, and repressing transcription from Pl BBa_R0063.

The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The right promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is up-regulated by the action of the Lux activator, LuxR complexed to HSL. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules the signalling compound homoserine lactone (HSL). This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: 2 silent point mutants were introduced in the coding sequence to remove internal XbaI and PstI sites. Mutation sites were chosen to replace codons commonly used in E. coli with codons used at a similar frequency.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr
